{"_id":"eCWoO60nqz2VK2gK","name":"Mental Disorder","permission":{"default":0,"qHi89sFcK4gHlOPd":3},"type":"trait","data":{"description":"<p>You have a psychological disorder from a previous traumatic experience. Choose one of the disorders listed on ▶224. This trait may be taken multiple times for different disorders.</p>","reference":"Eclipse Phase Second Edition p. 79","restrictions":"","triggers":"","source":"ego","state":{"level":0,"triggered":false},"levels":[{"cost":2,"effects":[{"type":"misc","unique":"","description":"You have a mental disorder (choose one)","id":"8gt3bi4mg8"}],"id":"vpnmgl4j2x"}],"subtype":"","traitType":"negative"},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"eJNC1QQgC1LLSd0f","name":"Contact","permission":{"default":0,"qHi89sFcK4gHlOPd":3},"type":"trait","data":{"description":"<p>You have a personal connection that you can rely on. This contact gives you a +10 modifier to tests with one particular rep network. You should work with your GM to establish the nature of this contact and why they help you. The GM ensures that a contact is not overused or abused and may have a contact occasionally call upon you for assistance as well. You may take this trait multiple times.</p>","reference":"Eclipse Phase Second Edition p. 73","restrictions":"","triggers":"","source":"ego","state":{"level":0,"triggered":false},"levels":[{"cost":1,"effects":[{"type":"successTest","tags":[{"type":"rep","network":"@Rep"}],"modifier":10,"toOpponent":false,"requirement":"","id":"kemtpal5y9"}],"id":"6kd2y61dsq"}],"subtype":"","traitType":"positive"},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"edX2GgMfpmuuKiMI","name":"Psi Vulnerability","permission":{"default":0,"qHi89sFcK4gHlOPd":3},"type":"trait","data":{"description":"<p>Psi sleights are particularly effective against your brain structure. Apply a -10 modifier per level when resisting psi. The morph trait may only be taken by morphs with biological brains.</p>","reference":"Eclipse Phase Second Edition p. 75","restrictions":"","triggers":"","source":"ego","state":{"level":0,"triggered":false},"levels":[{"cost":1,"effects":[{"type":"successTest","tags":[{"type":"aptitudeCheck","aptitude":"wil"}],"modifier":-10,"toOpponent":false,"requirement":"defending against psi sleights","id":"bcoxbq1lvt"}],"id":"rruqm6nxul"},{"cost":2,"effects":[{"type":"successTest","tags":[{"type":"aptitudeCheck","aptitude":"wil"}],"modifier":-20,"toOpponent":false,"requirement":"defending against psi sleights","id":"bcoxbq1lvt"}],"id":"00v7xlnkq9"}],"subtype":"","traitType":"negative"},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"ejks8xIjbYRsND4X","name":"Frailty","permission":{"default":0,"qHi89sFcK4gHlOPd":3},"type":"trait","data":{"description":"<p>The morph is not as resilient as similar models. Reduce Durability by 5. This will also decrease Wound Threshold (equal to DUR ÷ 5) and Death Rating (DUR × 1.5 for biomorphs, DUR × 2 for synthmorphs).</p>","reference":"Eclipse Phase Second Edition p. 78","restrictions":"","triggers":"","source":"morph","state":{"level":0,"triggered":false},"levels":[{"cost":2,"effects":[{"type":"health","health":"physical","stat":"derived","modifier":-5,"id":"yzyog2bq4a"}],"id":"6he2x7b7n8"},{"cost":4,"effects":[{"type":"health","health":"physical","stat":"derived","modifier":-10,"id":"5v4fbk5x76"}],"id":"rzmgjtf766"}],"subtype":"","traitType":"negative"},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"fAnaLc8b6O0bx4o7","name":"Weak Immune System","permission":{"default":0,"qHi89sFcK4gHlOPd":3},"type":"trait","data":{"description":"<p>This trait is only available to biomorphs. The morph’s immune system is easily compromised. Apply a -10 modifier per level when resisting the effects of diseases, drugs, chemicals, and toxins.</p>","reference":"Eclipse Phase Second Edition p. 80","restrictions":"","triggers":"","source":"morph","state":{"level":0,"triggered":false},"levels":[{"cost":1,"effects":[{"type":"successTest","tags":[{"type":"special","test":"resistSubstanceOrDisease"}],"modifier":-10,"toOpponent":false,"requirement":"","id":"qdf4v490il"}],"id":"2rsqpe0wjv"},{"cost":2,"effects":[{"type":"successTest","tags":[{"type":"special","test":"resistSubstanceOrDisease"}],"modifier":-20,"toOpponent":false,"requirement":"","id":"qdf4v490il"}],"id":"82uetxtlq7"}],"subtype":"","traitType":"negative"},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"fWFm0exfx2d5Vs3m","name":"Striking Looks","permission":{"default":0,"qHi89sFcK4gHlOPd":3},"type":"trait","data":{"description":"<p>Sculpted good looks are cheap and commonplace, but this morph possesses a physical look that can only be described as striking, fascinating, and unusual — even the gorgeous and chiseled glitterati take notice. Apply a +10 modifier to Persuade and Provoke tests where your allure may have an impact. Level 1 of this trait only applies to uplifts and synthmorphs; Level 2 is for humanoid biomorphs.</p>","reference":"Eclipse Phase Second Edition p. 76","restrictions":"","triggers":"","source":"morph","state":{"level":0,"triggered":false},"levels":[{"cost":1,"effects":[{"type":"successTest","tags":[{"type":"skill","skillType":"persuade"},{"type":"skill","skillType":"provoke"}],"modifier":10,"toOpponent":false,"requirement":"your allure may have an impact","id":"1im6277h03"}],"id":"8tgn0tunp5"},{"cost":2,"effects":[{"type":"successTest","tags":[{"type":"skill","skillType":"persuade"},{"type":"skill","skillType":"provoke"}],"modifier":10,"toOpponent":false,"requirement":"your allure may have an impact","id":"1im6277h03"}],"id":"67v0w7q70t"}],"subtype":"","traitType":"positive"},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"gLowZ31xCT2ThUtH","name":"Timidity","permission":{"default":0,"qHi89sFcK4gHlOPd":3},"type":"trait","data":{"description":"<p>You are weak-willed and easily intimidated. Apply -5 per level to WIL Checks.</p>","reference":"Eclipse Phase Second Edition p. 80","restrictions":"","triggers":"","source":"morph","state":{"level":0,"triggered":false},"levels":[{"cost":1,"effects":[{"type":"successTest","tags":[{"type":"aptitudeCheck","aptitude":"wil"}],"modifier":-5,"toOpponent":false,"requirement":"","id":"407jqnstuv"}],"id":"usek8aqgn7"},{"cost":2,"effects":[{"type":"successTest","tags":[{"type":"aptitudeCheck","aptitude":"wil"}],"modifier":-10,"toOpponent":false,"requirement":"","id":"407jqnstuv"}],"id":"8ecgvdm6xm"},{"cost":3,"effects":[{"type":"successTest","tags":[{"type":"aptitudeCheck","aptitude":"wil"}],"modifier":-15,"toOpponent":false,"requirement":"","id":"407jqnstuv"}],"id":"qbhx9f1su7"}],"subtype":"","traitType":"negative"},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"hK0Zc9LktoWiuCot","name":"Resources","permission":{"default":0,"qHi89sFcK4gHlOPd":3},"type":"trait","data":{"description":"<p>You have a measure of money, assets, and/or other wealth, as used in the inner system, hypercorp, Jovian, and Extropian polities. This provides bonus Morph Points and Gear Points equal to the trait's level when acquiring morphs ▶290 and gear ▶312. It also gives you a regular amount of disposable income to purchase gear during missions.</p><p>At Level 1, you can spend up to 2 GP per week on Minorcomplexity items given the appropriate time frame.</p><p>At Level 2, you can spend up to 3 GP per week on Minor or Moderate complexity items given the appropriate time frame.</p><p>At Level 3, you can spend up to 5 GP per week on items of any complexity, given the appropriate time frame.</p><p>Level 4 is the same as Level 3, except that you also have the capability to make even Rare and Restricted items available (at the gamemaster's discretion).</p><p>In most cases, acquiring the gear is simply a matter of exploiting your Resources trait and waiting the proper amount of time, assuming the desired item is available (Acquiring Gear During Missions ▶312). At the GM’s discretion, however, using Resources may require an appropriate Persuade Test (to convince another party to part ways with the item) or perhaps a Research Test (to find a source).</p><p>Levels 3 and 4 of this trait imply an amount of resources that deems you wealthy. To reflect this, you can use 2 of your weekly GP in conjunction with a Flex point for narrative control to say that you have a Moderate gear item immediately on hand in your home/ vehicle/personal possessions. You must have access to your personal possessions and (as with all uses of Flex for narrative control) the item must be plausible.</p><p>Resources can also apply as a modifier for certain tests. For example, if you attempt to bribe a triad goon or use your credit score to arrange a meeting with a potential business partner, apply a +10 modifier for each level of Resources you possess.</p><p>While Resources is an abstract measurement, players and GMs should use it as a rough benchmark for a character’s personal assets and lifestyle. A character with Level 1 might have their own cubicle in a beehive hab or a small apartment in a Martian dome or O’Neill cylinder’s working class areas, and they get around by bike or public transit. A character with Level 2 Resources might have a private residence on a small station or a condo in a larger hab, as well as a minicar or cycle to get around. A character with Level 3 could have a large residential complex or multiple homes, plus one or more vehicles. A Level 4 character is rich and might own a small private hab and even their own shuttle.</p><p>Your Resources trait may be affected by events in game. If your home is destroyed or you come across a secret cache of riches, the GM should adjust your trait level accordingly. You must pay the extra cost in Rez Points if your trait goes up, but you receive an RP credit if your wealth goes down.</p><p>In desperate circumstances, you may also intentionally burn your Resources to refresh your weekly GP to get something you urgently need (or get it more quickly). This represents the expenditure of all or major portions of your assets with no hope of reclaiming them and no RP reimbursement. The GM should reduce your Resources trait level by an amount appropriate to the transaction.</p>","reference":"Eclipse Phase Second Edition p. 75","restrictions":"","triggers":"","source":"ego","state":{"level":0,"triggered":false},"levels":[{"cost":2,"effects":[{"type":"misc","unique":"","description":"You can spend up to 2 GP per week on Minor complexity items given the appropriate time frame","id":"ljwq8ae2jw"},{"type":"successTest","tags":[{"type":"skillCategory","category":"social"}],"modifier":10,"toOpponent":false,"requirement":"using your wealth","id":"z3hn7x0sey"}],"id":"9ijgbb3gal"},{"cost":4,"effects":[{"type":"misc","unique":"","description":"You can spend up to 3 GP per week on Minor or Moderate complexity items given the appropriate time frame","id":"brqkznj3f8"},{"type":"successTest","tags":[{"type":"skillCategory","category":"social"}],"modifier":20,"toOpponent":false,"requirement":"using your wealth","id":"1iccyhdw0c"}],"id":"xv1h55zz9y"},{"cost":6,"effects":[{"type":"misc","unique":"","description":"You can spend up to 5 GP per week on items of any complexity, given the appropriate time frame","id":"35r60wmgsk"},{"type":"successTest","tags":[{"type":"skillCategory","category":"social"}],"modifier":30,"toOpponent":false,"requirement":"using your wealth","id":"3jv6wz6w2r"}],"id":"qnxwlef0ai"},{"cost":8,"effects":[{"type":"misc","unique":"","description":"You can spend up to 5 GP per week on items of any complexity, given the appropriate time frame, this may also include Rare or Restricted items (GM's discretion)","id":"xw9oenib36"},{"type":"successTest","tags":[{"type":"skillCategory","category":"social"}],"modifier":40,"toOpponent":false,"requirement":"using your wealth","id":"pieapwjcaq"}],"id":"ekalh2g5g3"}],"subtype":"","traitType":"positive"},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"htg63tWKwQNFVPsi","name":"Timidity","permission":{"default":0,"qHi89sFcK4gHlOPd":3},"type":"trait","data":{"description":"<p>You are weak-willed and easily intimidated. Apply -5 per level to WIL Checks.</p>","reference":"Eclipse Phase Second Edition","restrictions":"","triggers":"","source":"ego","state":{"level":0,"triggered":false},"levels":[{"cost":1,"effects":[{"type":"successTest","tags":[{"type":"aptitudeCheck","aptitude":"wil"}],"modifier":-5,"toOpponent":false,"requirement":"","id":"gag18366rc"}],"id":"k6pkoios4n"},{"cost":2,"effects":[{"type":"successTest","tags":[{"type":"aptitudeCheck","aptitude":"wil"}],"modifier":-10,"toOpponent":false,"requirement":"","id":"gag18366rc"}],"id":"5vnqtbi2k1"},{"cost":3,"effects":[{"type":"successTest","tags":[{"type":"aptitudeCheck","aptitude":"wil"}],"modifier":-15,"toOpponent":false,"requirement":"","id":"gag18366rc"}],"id":"4ktwykblla"}],"subtype":"","traitType":"negative"},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"hzvftjF3K2THTcrP","name":"Pain Tolerance","permission":{"default":0,"qHi89sFcK4gHlOPd":3},"type":"trait","data":{"description":"<p>You have a high threshold for pain, enabling you to shrug off the effects of pain on your abilities and concentration. You ignore the -10 modifier for 1 wound per level. This trait is compatible with other pain-resistant effects, but a maximum of 3 wound effects may be ignored.</p>","reference":"Eclipse Phase Second Edition p. 74","restrictions":"","triggers":"","source":"ego","state":{"level":0,"triggered":false},"levels":[{"cost":2,"effects":[{"type":"health","health":"physical","stat":"woundsIgnored","modifier":1,"id":"j6esr2wk9e"}],"id":"lymgnh7up6"},{"cost":4,"effects":[{"type":"health","health":"physical","stat":"woundsIgnored","modifier":2,"id":"j6esr2wk9e"}],"id":"d61dkn1toc"}],"subtype":"","traitType":"positive"},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"i3BXaTxIaFtEQvVo","name":"Limberness","permission":{"default":0,"qHi89sFcK4gHlOPd":3},"type":"trait","data":{"description":"<p>The morph is especially flexible and supple, capable of graceful contortions and interesting positions. At Level 1 , you can do the splits, smoke with your toes, and squeeze into small, cramped spaces. At Level 2, you are a double-jointed escape artist. Apply a +10 modifier per level to escape bonds, fit into small spaces, contort, or otherwise rely on flexibility.</p>","reference":"Eclipse Phase Second Edition p. 74","restrictions":"","triggers":"","source":"morph","state":{"level":0,"triggered":false},"levels":[{"cost":1,"effects":[{"type":"successTest","tags":[{"type":"allActions"}],"modifier":10,"toOpponent":false,"requirement":"escaping bonds, fitting into small spaces, contorting, or otherwise relying on flexibility.","id":"6eo3gq4h8y"}],"id":"9hdc4cclwf"},{"cost":2,"effects":[{"type":"successTest","tags":[{"type":"allActions"}],"modifier":20,"toOpponent":false,"requirement":"escaping bonds, fitting into small spaces, contorting, or otherwise relying on flexibility.","id":"6eo3gq4h8y"}],"id":"oaf2mka0bv"}],"subtype":"","traitType":"positive"},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"icWTfzn8iH1PSyeY","name":"Low Pain Tolerance","permission":{"default":0,"qHi89sFcK4gHlOPd":3},"type":"trait","data":{"description":"<p>Pain is your enemy. You have a very low threshold for pain tolerance; increase the modifier for each wound taken by an additional -10 (so the character suffers -20 with one wound, -40 with a second, -60 with a third, etc.).</p><p>Additionally, you suffer a -30 modifier on both SOM Checks and other tests that involve pain resistance. The morph version of this trait is only available for biomorphs.</p>","reference":"Eclipse Phase Second Edition p. 78","restrictions":"","triggers":"","source":"ego","state":{"level":0,"triggered":false},"levels":[{"cost":4,"effects":[{"type":"health","health":"physical","stat":"woundModifier","modifier":-10,"id":"04j3r9heci"},{"type":"successTest","tags":[{"type":"aptitudeCheck","aptitude":"som"},{"type":"special","test":"painResistance"}],"modifier":-30,"toOpponent":false,"requirement":"","id":"chfycaan3t"}],"id":"fu396voqqy"}],"subtype":"","traitType":"negative"},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"iqYExft1aT9daMJN","name":"Age","permission":{"default":0,"qHi89sFcK4gHlOPd":3},"type":"trait","data":{"description":"<p>This trait may only be applied to flat and splicer morphs. The morph is physically aged and has not been rejuvenated. Old morphs are increasingly uncommon, though some people adopt them hoping to gain an air of seniority and respectability. Apply a -10 modifier on all physical actions.</p>","reference":"Eclipse Phase Second Edition p. 76","restrictions":"","triggers":"","source":"morph","state":{"level":0,"triggered":false},"levels":[{"cost":4,"effects":[{"type":"successTest","tags":[{"type":"action","subtype":"physical"}],"modifier":-10,"toOpponent":false,"requirement":"","id":"fzq9262w8n"}],"id":"vnzaemvkye"}],"subtype":"","traitType":"negative"},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"jGzKaUpuVzMr8PbP","name":"Inherent Flaws","permission":{"default":0,"qHi89sFcK4gHlOPd":3},"type":"trait","data":{"description":"<p>This trait is only available for synthmorphs. This particular morph has some unfixable flaws and inevitably breaks down. Any time a critical failure is rolled, there is a 10% chance the morph also acquires a wound.</p>","reference":"Eclipse Phase Second Edition p. 78","restrictions":"","triggers":"","source":"morph","state":{"level":0,"triggered":false},"levels":[{"cost":2,"effects":[{"type":"misc","unique":"","description":"Any time you critically fail a roll, there's a 10% chance you acquire a wound","id":"cum5gy6imu"}],"id":"ovqaodfv7g"}],"subtype":"","traitType":"negative"},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"jvbcJUVGQhHw5yUV","name":"Addiction","permission":{"default":0,"qHi89sFcK4gHlOPd":3},"type":"trait","data":{"description":"<p>You have a pathological reliance on a drug ▶330, stimulus (e.g., XP, VR), or activity (e.g., mesh use, dying) to a degree that impacts your physical or mental health. Addiction comes in two forms: mental (affecting the ego) and physical (affecting the biomorph). Work with your GM to choose an addiction that is appropriate for your game. You must indulge in your addiction at a regular frequency according to the level or go into withdrawal. Withdrawal inflicts a -10 modifier per level.</p><p>Level 1: Once per week. Your minor addiction is largely kept under control — it does not ruin your life, though it may create difficulties. You may not even recognize or admit you have a problem.</p><p>Level 2: Once per day. Your moderate addiction is in full swing and often causes you to neglect other aspects of your life.</p><p>Level 3: Once per 6 hours. You face major cravings, live for your next fix, and are on the road to ruin.</p><p>Addiction is triggered in the same way as disorders ▶224. Triggers include the presence of the addiction's focus, fear, frustration, helplessness, and violence.</p><p>Every addiction takes different forms, depending on the character and source. Long-term addiction may result in physical or mental damage (impairment modifiers or reductions to SOM Checks or WIL Checks) and may build up tolerance, requiring higher dosages. At the GM’s discretion, you may need to make WIL Checks to avoid raising the addiction level. Withdrawal may also inflict additional effects such as mood swings, compulsive behavior, or physical sickness.</p><p>You may kick the habit by staying clean for 1 week per level. Resisting the craving, however, requires a WIL Check every day, modified by the source’s addiction modifier. Once the addiction is kicked, however, there is always the possibility of a relapse. GMs may call for WIL Checks anytime you are directly tempted or undergo substantial stress or mental trauma.</p><p>If you upload, fork, or resleeve, any mental addictions persist with your ego/fork; physical addictions remain with the morph. This trait may be taken more than once for different addictions. The morph version of this trait only applies to biomorphs.</p>","reference":"Eclipse Phase Second Edition p. 76","restrictions":"","triggers":"","source":"morph","state":{"level":0,"triggered":false},"levels":[{"cost":1,"effects":[{"type":"successTest","tags":[{"type":"allActions"}],"modifier":-10,"toOpponent":false,"requirement":"not indulged in: once per week","id":"3308tsh3uf"}],"id":"x0hl4cimcc"},{"cost":2,"effects":[{"type":"successTest","tags":[{"type":"allActions"}],"modifier":-20,"toOpponent":false,"requirement":"not indulged in: once per day","id":"2ssqll2zxb"}],"id":"pshr4a2hxk"},{"cost":4,"effects":[{"type":"successTest","tags":[{"type":"allActions"}],"modifier":-30,"toOpponent":false,"requirement":"not indulged in: once per 6 hours","id":"rs2gen970s"}],"id":"sosdectydg"}],"subtype":"","traitType":"negative"},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"kNf9vjoUlzilBH5x","name":"Identity Crisis","permission":{"default":0,"qHi89sFcK4gHlOPd":3},"type":"trait","data":{"description":"<p>Resleeving is not an easy process. You are stuck with the mental image of your original body and have trouble adapting to your new morphs’ looks and physiologies. You have difficulty identifying yourself in mirrors, photos, or sensor feeds. You also tend to move in ways inappropriate to your new forms, such as attempting to walk instead of using new limbs or propulsion systems, forgetting to duck when walking through doorways, becoming alarmed by new sensory inputs, etc. You should roleplay this trait accordingly, and may suffer a -10 modifier to applicable actions.</p>","reference":"Eclipse Phase Second Edition p. 78","restrictions":"","triggers":"","source":"ego","state":{"level":0,"triggered":false},"levels":[{"cost":1,"effects":[{"type":"misc","unique":"","description":"You have trouble adapting to your looks and physiology. You may suffer a -10 to applicable \nactions","id":"mng2wks1oh"}],"id":"xj6w9kwpxl"}],"subtype":"","traitType":"negative"},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"kVq0kLSdqZso5krq","name":"Superior Numeracy","permission":{"default":0,"qHi89sFcK4gHlOPd":3},"type":"trait","data":{"description":"<p>You are quite good with numbers. Apply a +10 per level to Know and Technical Tests that directly involve math.</p>","reference":"Eclipse Phase Second Edition p. 76","restrictions":"","triggers":"","source":"ego","state":{"level":0,"triggered":false},"levels":[{"cost":2,"effects":[{"type":"successTest","tags":[{"type":"fieldSkill","fieldSkill":"know","field":""},{"type":"skillCategory","category":"technical"}],"modifier":10,"toOpponent":false,"requirement":"involving math","id":"7djy4m4u9m"}],"id":"5jtjfqtddr"},{"cost":4,"effects":[{"type":"successTest","tags":[{"type":"fieldSkill","fieldSkill":"know","field":""},{"type":"skillCategory","category":"technical"}],"modifier":20,"toOpponent":false,"requirement":"involving math","id":"7djy4m4u9m"}],"id":"67m5rcxw1u"}],"subtype":"","traitType":"positive"},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"kVtL336ksL9JJFsm","name":"Innocuous Looks","permission":{"default":0,"qHi89sFcK4gHlOPd":3},"type":"trait","data":{"description":"<p>Thanks to mass-produced designs and sculpted media-star composite visages, your cookie-cutter looks are so mundane as to be indistinguishable. It is difficult to pick your common-place face out of the crowd, describe its appearance, or otherwise remember physical details. Apply a -10 modifier to tests made to spot, describe, or remember you; this does not apply to psi or mesh searches. This trait may not be applied to any morph with an Availability lower than 50.</p>","reference":"Eclipse Phase Second Edition p. 74","restrictions":"","triggers":"","source":"morph","state":{"level":0,"triggered":false},"levels":[{"cost":1,"effects":[{"type":"misc","unique":"","description":"-10 modifier to spot, describe, or remember you","id":"r6f60msf25"}],"id":"c8m4xxeao1"}],"subtype":"","traitType":"positive"},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"kfEC9rsDxGAncuYD","name":"Lethal","permission":{"default":0,"qHi89sFcK4gHlOPd":3},"type":"trait","data":{"description":"<p>This morph inflicts more damage in melee combat. Add +1d6 DV to all melee damage rolls.</p>","reference":"Eclipse Phase Second Edition p. 74","restrictions":"","triggers":"","source":"morph","state":{"level":0,"triggered":false},"levels":[{"cost":1,"effects":[{"type":"melee","dvModifier":"1d6","id":"g6d8u65phh"}],"id":"t34p3c3pfi"}],"subtype":"","traitType":"positive"},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"kgurDAq2LTI4Z1YN","name":"Hardening","permission":{"default":0,"qHi89sFcK4gHlOPd":3},"type":"trait","data":{"description":"<p>You are accustomed to trauma, but it has scarred you. You are immune to stress from either alienation, helplessness, or violence (choose one). However, your WIL Check is reduced by 10 and you suffer a -10 modifier on Persuade Tests. This trait may be taken multiple times for different types of stress; modifiers are cumulative.</p>","reference":"Eclipse Phase Second Edition p. 74","restrictions":"","triggers":"","source":"ego","state":{"level":0,"triggered":false},"levels":[{"cost":1,"effects":[{"type":"successTest","tags":[{"type":"aptitudeCheck","aptitude":"wil"},{"type":"skill","skillType":"persuade"}],"modifier":-10,"toOpponent":false,"requirement":"","id":"euaptbbfqt"},{"type":"misc","unique":"","description":"You are immune to either alienation, helplessness or violence (choose one)","id":"8695grtuz3"}],"id":"7d96iwswbe"}],"subtype":"","traitType":"positive"},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"l12ee2txIMKxDdVw","name":"Memory Artifact","permission":{"default":0,"qHi89sFcK4gHlOPd":3},"type":"trait","data":{"description":"<p>A previous ego&rsquo;s memories somehow survived the wiping process and linger on in this morph&rsquo;s brain/hardware. Once per session, a memory from this past occupant resurfaces in your mind. These memories are often emotionally charged and jarring; make a COG Check or suffer SV 1d6. These memories integrate into your own, though they may be erased with psychosurgery.</p>\n<p>Work with your GM to decide the specifics of the memories. GMs should use these recall incidents for plot purposes; they may reveal sensitive data, incriminating evidence, secrets hidden from the public, or details the previous ego does not want spread.</p>","reference":"Eclipse Phase Second Edition p. 78","restrictions":"","triggers":"","source":"morph","state":{"level":0,"triggered":false},"levels":[{"cost":1,"effects":[{"type":"misc","unique":"","description":"Once per session: a memory from this morph's past occupant resurfaces in your mind.","id":"3or5w1zq3z"}],"id":"jklbinoiw9"}],"subtype":"","traitType":"negative"},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"l3Ogd00RptctTLST","name":"Quickness","permission":{"default":0,"qHi89sFcK4gHlOPd":3},"type":"trait","data":{"description":"<p>Either your morph is dexterous or you take full advantage of its nimbleness. Apply +5 per level to REF Checks.</p>","reference":"Eclipse Phase Second Edition p. 75","restrictions":"","triggers":"","source":"morph","state":{"level":0,"triggered":false},"levels":[{"cost":1,"effects":[{"type":"successTest","tags":[{"type":"aptitudeCheck","aptitude":"ref"}],"modifier":5,"toOpponent":false,"requirement":"","id":"x6kpekczzn"}],"id":"euvg8vjx60"},{"cost":2,"effects":[{"type":"successTest","tags":[{"type":"aptitudeCheck","aptitude":"ref"}],"modifier":10,"toOpponent":false,"requirement":"","id":"x6kpekczzn"}],"id":"5iu5tsvpmb"},{"cost":3,"effects":[{"type":"successTest","tags":[{"type":"aptitudeCheck","aptitude":"ref"}],"modifier":15,"toOpponent":false,"requirement":"","id":"x6kpekczzn"}],"id":"yequhq11it"}],"subtype":"","traitType":"positive"},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"lLlfizNcVwaxnNyY","name":"Non-Human Biochemistry","permission":{"default":0,"qHi89sFcK4gHlOPd":3},"type":"trait","data":{"description":"<p>This trait is only available to biomorphs. This morph has substantial physiological and genetic differences from human morphs. Level 1 applies to non-human morphs. Level 2 applies to non-mammalian morphs. Apply a -10 modifier per level to Medicine Tests. Certain drugs, toxin, chemicals, or medical procedures may not work or may have a different effect (GM discretion). This trait may not be applied to morphs that do not come with it.</p>","reference":"Eclipse Phase Second Edition p. 79","restrictions":"","triggers":"","source":"morph","state":{"level":0,"triggered":false},"levels":[{"cost":2,"effects":[{"type":"successTest","tags":[{"type":"fieldSkill","fieldSkill":"medicine","field":""}],"modifier":-10,"toOpponent":false,"requirement":"working on this morph","id":"4hpg27idjb"}],"id":"9jdoqitzoh"},{"cost":4,"effects":[{"type":"successTest","tags":[{"type":"fieldSkill","fieldSkill":"medicine","field":""}],"modifier":-20,"toOpponent":false,"requirement":"working on this morph","id":"4hpg27idjb"}],"id":"c2habh6yun"}],"subtype":"","traitType":"negative"},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
