{"_id":"reczmRGJKNKNMutj","name":"Instability","permission":{"default":0,"qHi89sFcK4gHlOPd":3},"type":"trait","data":{"description":"<p>Your mental foundation has serious cracks. Reduce your Lucidity by 5 per level. This also affects derived stats based on Lucidity; reduce both your Trauma Threshold by 1 and your Insanity Rating by 10 per level.</p>","reference":"Eclipse Phase Second Edition p. 78","restrictions":"","triggers":"","source":"ego","state":{"level":0,"triggered":false},"levels":[{"cost":2,"effects":[{"type":"health","health":"mental","stat":"durability","modifier":-5,"id":"yqj662hpid"},{"type":"health","health":"mental","stat":"woundThreshold","modifier":-1,"id":"0femvb5gx4"},{"type":"health","health":"mental","stat":"deathRating","modifier":-10,"id":"gnebp1talq"}],"id":"ytuvzoak3h"},{"cost":4,"effects":[{"type":"health","health":"mental","stat":"durability","modifier":-10,"id":"yqj662hpid"},{"type":"health","health":"mental","stat":"woundThreshold","modifier":-2,"id":"0femvb5gx4"},{"type":"health","health":"mental","stat":"deathRating","modifier":-20,"id":"gnebp1talq"}],"id":"1bu9f42393"}],"subtype":"","traitType":"negative"},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"sNk3x5nAjy28GYcd","name":"Common Sense","permission":{"default":0,"qHi89sFcK4gHlOPd":3},"type":"trait","data":{"description":"<p>Your innate sense of judgment cuts through distractions and other factors that might cloud a decision. Once per game session, you may ask the GM what choice to make or course of action to take; the GM will give you solid advice based on what your character knows. Alternatively, if you are about to make a disastrous decision, the GM can use your free hint to warn you that you are making a grave mistake.</p>","reference":"Eclipse Phase Second Edition p. 73","restrictions":"","triggers":"","source":"ego","state":{"level":0,"triggered":false},"levels":[{"cost":2,"effects":[{"type":"misc","unique":"","description":"Once per session: may ask the GM for best advice or the GM can use a hint to warn you","id":"m5hrpukkk3"}],"id":"yefk6qf2et"}],"subtype":"","traitType":"positive"},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"sdlI49owS4qAqRZC","name":"Low Pain Tolerance","permission":{"default":0,"qHi89sFcK4gHlOPd":3},"type":"trait","data":{"description":"<p>Pain is your enemy. You have a very low threshold for pain tolerance; increase the modifier for each wound taken by an additional -10 (so the character suffers -20 with one wound, -40 with a second, -60 with a third, etc.).</p><p>Additionally, you suffer a -30 modifier on both SOM Checks and other tests that involve pain resistance. The morph version of this trait is only available for biomorphs.</p>","reference":"Eclipse Phase Second Edition p. 78","restrictions":"","triggers":"","source":"morph","state":{"level":0,"triggered":false},"levels":[{"cost":4,"effects":[{"type":"health","health":"physical","stat":"woundModifier","modifier":-10,"id":"rhojfhjlpy"},{"type":"successTest","tags":[{"type":"aptitudeCheck","aptitude":"som"},{"type":"special","test":"painResistance"}],"modifier":-30,"toOpponent":false,"requirement":"","id":"5po69pudc2"}],"id":"abxyi9nvc6"}],"subtype":"","traitType":"negative"},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"t18CsOdw5O2cFI97","name":"Patron","permission":{"default":0,"qHi89sFcK4gHlOPd":3},"type":"trait","data":{"description":"<p>There is an influential person in your life who can be relied on for occasional support. This could be a wealthy hyperelite family member, a high-ranking triad boss, or an anarchist networker with an unbeatable reputation. When called upon, this patron can pull strings, supply resources, make introductions, or bail you out of trouble. Work with your GM to define this NPC, your relationship, and why they support you (familial obligation? childhood buddies? you saved their life once?).</p><p>The patron provides one free major favor ▶308 per story arc, no test necessary. GMs should be careful that this trait does not get abused. Smaller favors are beneath the patron’s concern. If the character asks for too much, too often, the patron’s support may dry up. On occasion, the patron may call upon the character for favors as well.</p>","reference":"Eclipse Phase Second Edition p. 74","restrictions":"","triggers":"","source":"ego","state":{"level":0,"triggered":false},"levels":[{"cost":6,"effects":[{"type":"misc","unique":"","description":"One free major favor per story arc, no test necessary","id":"w6q8p8fjs8"}],"id":"ka2850j8x5"}],"subtype":"","traitType":"positive"},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"va6795gyy9eTSZcn","name":"Neural Damage","permission":{"default":0,"qHi89sFcK4gHlOPd":3},"type":"trait","data":{"description":"<p>You suffered some type of neurological damage that cannot yet be cured. The affliction is part of your ego and remains even when resleeving. This damage may have been inherited, resulted from a poorly designed morph or implant, or inflicted by a nanovirus during the Fall. Work with your GM to agree on a specific disorder appropriate to your game. The GM may inflict impairment modifiers (usually -10) as appropriate, according to the affliction. Some possibilities are:</p><p>Amusica: You have an inability to make or understand music. Automatically fail music-related skill tests.</p><p>Color Blindness: You cannot distinguish color, only variations in brightness. -10 to visual Perceive Tests.</p><p>Lack Depth Perception: You have difficulty ascertaining distance. Double range modifiers.</p><p>Lack Face Recognition: You cannot distinguish faces. -10 to visual Perceive Tests involving person identification.</p><p>Logorrhea: You use an excessive amount of words and sometimes can’t stop talking. -10 to Persuade and verbal Provoke Tests.</p><p>Mood Swings: Your emotions shift quickly and dramatically. -10 to WIL Checks against Provoke.</p><p>Partial Aphasia: You sometimes have difficulty communicating or using words. -10 to Persuade and verbal Provoke Tests.</p><p>Repetitive Behavior: You unwillingly repeat your actions. You unwillingly repeat your actions. Make a COG Check to avoid repeating your actions when under pressure.</p><p>Synaesthesia: Some types of sensory input are conflated with other perceptual phenomena.</p><p>This trait may be taken multiple times, for different afflictions.</p>","reference":"Eclipse Phase Second Edition p. 79","restrictions":"","triggers":"","source":"ego","state":{"level":0,"triggered":false},"levels":[{"cost":2,"effects":[{"type":"misc","unique":"","description":"You suffer from neurological damage and are afflicted with a disorder (choose one)","id":"yjdxjnzba7"}],"id":"gtuwfw4t4u"}],"subtype":"","traitType":"negative"},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
